table asyncio_extra151.asyncio_dict_len_and_class:
  description: "asyncio.__dict__ size and class name checks in asynciodict151 namespace — asyncio.__dict__.__len__()==136 (the asyncio package exports 136 names; compare submodules: tasks=81, futures=40, locks=21, queues=20; asyncio is the aggregating package re-exporting from all submodules); asyncio.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('dict')==True (module __dict__ is a plain dict, not a mappingproxy — only class __dict__ objects are mappingproxy; len('dict')==4); asyncio.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==4; asyncio.__name__.__eq__('asyncio')==True (len=7: the module name); asyncio.__name__.__len__()==7; NEW in extra151: first asyncio.__dict__ size and class name spec in asynciodict151 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
